# Homepage Content Editing

- Treat user instructions, wording, and prompts as editing intent, not page copy.
- Do not paste meta-instructions or conversational phrasing into public homepage content.
- Rewrite content in polished academic language appropriate for the target page.
- Keep the homepage concise; move detailed project process, contribution lists, and implementation notes to the research experience page.
